AS South African cricket grapples with the Black Lives Matter (BLM) movement, former Proteas fast bowler Makhaya Ntini has revealed that he often felt lonely throughout his international career. In an interview with SABC Morning Live, Ntini made a startling revelation that he often felt lonely throughout his international career. Ntini recalled an incident where he would run instead of using the team bus to commute between hotels and stadiums as his team-mates would often avoid sitting with him. 